{
  "texts": [
    "The research by Ángel Casado Hidalgo et al (2021) examined the potential of Deep Learning and Meta-Learning in the context of predicting student performance.",
    "The DNNs model was manually created using tried-and-true methods of searching for the best neural architecture and optimizing the parameter values.",
    "AutoKeras recommends a Meta-Learning model because it has fewer layers and parameters, and it has been demonstrated that models with the same performance can be produced with less effort.",
    "The characteristics were obtained from 5,066 records on the Sakai educational platform, which was used by 500 students at the International University of La Rioja to enroll in the four courses.",
    "Filter methods such as analysis of variance (ANOVA) and recursive elimination (RFECV) were used to select features."
  ]
}